Package: irelr
Type: Package
Title: Pedigree inference using molecular marker data
Version: 0.0.1
Date: 2015-01-05
Authors@R: c(person("Anders", "Gonçalves da Silva",email = "andersgs@gmail.com",role = c("aut","cre")),
  person("Michael A.", "Russello", email = "michael.russello@ubc.ca",role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Anders Gonçalves da Silva <andersgs@gmail.com>
Description: irelr is an R implementation of iRel, a software designed to infer 
    pedigree relationships using molecular marker data. A number of 
    relatedness indices are calculated, and Monte Carlo 
    simulations are performed to determine confidence in classifying 
    pairs of individuals into different relatedness categories.
License: GPLv2
Imports: 
  adegenet,
  ape,
  hierfstat,
  knitr,
  ggplot2,
  reshape2
Suggests: knitr
VignetteBuilder: knitr
